RuntimeException(13): Cursor session id (11e88ca9-f7b5-48d7-9e8e-95511a1e6a22 - pzarhKY2owve6qhN2jyojBF8O3wMotRKbXhCmcmZSlE=) is not the same as the operation context's session id (625e9fdc-4d33-48e0-8cf1-e9e359ba17a1 - pzarhKY2owve6qhN2jyojBF8O3wMotRKbXhCmcmZSlE=)
aggregate command with lsid: 11e88ca9f7b548d79e8e95511a1e6a22
killCursors command with lsid: 625e9fdc4d3348e08cf1e9e359ba17a1
getMore command with lsid: 625e9fdc4d3348e08cf1e9e359ba17a1
RuntimeException(13): Cursor session id (11e88ca9-f7b5-48d7-9e8e-95511a1e6a22 - pzarhKY2owve6qhN2jyojBF8O3wMotRKbXhCmcmZSlE=) is not the same as the operation context's session id (625e9fdc-4d33-48e0-8cf1-e9e359ba17a1 - pzarhKY2owve6qhN2jyojBF8O3wMotRKbXhCmcmZSlE=)
killCursors command with lsid: 625e9fdc4d3348e08cf1e9e359ba17a1
{noformat}

The killCursors output is the result of a previous cursor object being freed because it has a non-zero cursor ID. You'll note that the session ID used for killCursors corresponds to the previous getMore responsible for the preceding exception.

Here we see that find cursors have no problem reusing the correct session ID for their getMore commands; however, aggregate cursors seem to check a new implicit session out of the LIFO pool each time, regardless of whether the original aggregate used an implicit or explicit session.

{{config.m4}} currently defines {{developer-flags}} and {{coverage}} enable options. For static builds, these could conflict with other extensions. We should prefix them with "mongodb".

Since both of these options are intended for internal usage, BC should not be a concern and we can simply rename them.

That would leave only the following options without prefixes, both of which are already deprecated:

 * {{PHP_ARG_WITH([openssl-dir])}}
 * {{PHP_ARG_WITH([system-ciphers])}}

In [this thread on mongodb-user|https://groups.google.com/d/msg/mongodb-user/L2_NvgygMvo/LuwzQeyOCQAJ], a user reported sporadic authentication failures with SCRAM-SHA-1 in both FPM and CLI environments. The following code is used to connect:

{code:php}
$sslContext = stream_context_create([
        "ssl" => [
                "verify_peer" => false,
                "verify_peer_name" => false,
                "allow_self_signed" => true,
        ],
]);

$this->client = new MongoDB\Client(
        'mongodb://db1:27017,db2:27017,db3:27017/',
        [
                'username'               => $this->conOpts['username'],
                'password'               => $this->conOpts['password'],
                'ssl'                    => true,
                'replicaSet'             => $this->conOpts['replicaSet'],
                'authSource'             => $this->conOpts['db'],
        ],
        [
                'context' => $sslContext,
                'typeMap' => ['root' => 'array', 'document' => 'array', 'array' => 'array']
        ]
);
{code}

This error only started appearing in PHPC 1.3.0, which leads me to believe it may be related to some change in libmongoc between 1.5.5 (used by PHPC 1.2.x) and 1.8.0 (used by PHPC 1.3.0). It's possible this may be related to SCRAM-SHA-1 caching introduced in [fc3ff3b|https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-c-driver/commit/fc3ff3bdbcce8a1dfc86a2c9a10e4943a3c8eb10] for CDRIVER-2150.

[~scott.lhommedieu] shared an example of client metadata logs, which make it impossible to determine the PHP version:

{noformat}
cfg=0x156b8e9 posix=200809 stdc=201112 CC=GCC 5.4.0 20160609 CFLAGS='-g -O2 -fPIE -fstack-protector-strong -Wformat -Werror=format-security -Wall -ped...
{noformat}

Ideally, the output would include the PHP version at the end:

{noformat}
cfg=0x30c9 posix=200809 CC=GCC 4.8.5 20150623 (Red Hat 4.8.5-11) CFLAGS='-g -O2' LDFLAGS='' / PHP 7.1.6
{noformat}

The PHP version string [appended during MINIT|https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-php-driver/blob/1.6.0alpha1/php_phongo.c#L2906] (via [{{mongoc_handshake_data_append}}|https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-c-driver/blob/1.14.0/src/libmongoc/src/mongoc/mongoc-handshake.c#L565]) is cut off during construction of the handshake document ([{{_mongoc_handshake_build_doc_with_application}}|https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-c-driver/blob/1.14.0/src/libmongoc/src/mongoc/mongoc-handshake.c#L465] and [{{_append_platform_field}}|https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-c-driver/blob/1.14.0/src/libmongoc/src/mongoc/mongoc-handshake.c#L430]). This is likely caused by libmongoc first appending user-set CFLAGS and LDFLAGS in [{{set_platform_string}}|https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-c-driver/blob/1.14.0/src/libmongoc/src/mongoc/mongoc-handshake.c#L364]. Those arguably have less value than the PHP version, so we should consider leaving those constants unset in [{{config.m4}}|https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-php-driver/blob/1.6.0alpha1/config.m4#L286] or propose that libmongoc swap the order of appended platform fields so that data from the wrapping driver (e.g. {{ext-mongodb}}) is included before CFLAGS/LDFLAGS.
